|---|---|
|<font color=#FF3399>[1]</font> The G7 has established a "coordination mechanism" to help Ukraine "repair, restore and defend its critical energy and water infrastructure," the group's foreign ministers said in a joint statement on Friday following meetings in Mnster.<a href="https://www.cnn.com/europe/live-news/russia-ukraine-war-news-11-04-22/h_c385d6702ae33392504bd3ccdb00d096" target="_blank">Source</a>| The G7 has established a "coordination mechanism" to help Ukraine "repair, restore and defend its critical energy and water infrastructure," the group's foreign ministers said in a joint statement on Friday following meetings in Mnster. The statement condemned Russia's attacks against civilians and civilian infrastructure, "in particular energy and water facilities" in Ukraine.|
|<font color=#FF3399>[2]</font> The European Commission on Wednesday proposed an 18 billion-euro financial support package for Ukraine that would include funding for Kyiv to restore critical infrastructure.<a href="https://www.foxnews.com/health/ukraines-power-outages-russian-air-strikes-pose-challenge-critically-ill" target="_blank">Source</a>| Government officials working with international partners had delivered more than 400 generators to hospitals nationwide, he said. Another 1,100 were expected from a joint project with the World Bank and 170 more from the World Health Organization. The European Commission on Wednesday proposed an 18 billion-euro financial support package for Ukraine that would include funding for Kyiv to restore critical infrastructure. Meanwhile, Halytska and the 27 other patients suffering from kidney diseases in the Obukhiv hospital have to lie back and wait for the next gap in the power cuts.|
